A cyberpunk cityscape at night showing a massive crowd of ordinary citizens walking through a neon-lit German street, each person surrounded by floating holographic surveillance drones and scanning beams. Giant digital billboards tower overhead displaying eye symbols and biometric scanning grids. The atmosphere is oppressive with harsh red and blue lighting cutting through smog. Security cameras mounted on every surface point downward like accusatory fingers. The citizens appear as silhouettes, anonymous and interchangeable, while their data streams upward in glowing particle trails toward a dark central tower. Rain falls through laser grid patterns that section the crowd into trackable zones. The mood is dystopian and paranoid, suggesting everyone is being watched and catalogued.
